First time that I have ordered delivery and it was not a great experience compared to their competition.  Order was late and not surprisingly cold, reasons as that the driver forgot the Pizza...  everything was cold, burger had one fresh bun on top and a stale one on the bottom.  Burger patty tasted nice, although cold...  pizza came in glad wrap, not in a box as they ran out.  Chilli chicken was nice

The Mansarover family run business serves excellent Indian cuisine from a rustic setting within the shadow of the Tung Chung fort. Specials are Dahl Makhani (butter lentils) and the chicken Tikka Masala. Fries, burgers and pizzas also on the menu for kids who don't like indian spice. All dishes can be made to order to suit the required level of spiciness. Personal faves are the Chicken Tikka, saag paneer, all the curries are good and the garlic naan.
The best indian restaurant in Tung Chung
